Methodological choices in brucellosis burden of disease assessments: A 
systematic review.

Di Bari C(1)(2), Venkateswaran N(1)(3), Bruce M(1)(4), Fastl C(1)(2), Huntington 
B(1)(5)(6), Patterson GT(1)(7), Rushton J(1)(5), Torgerson P(1)(8), Pigott 
DM(1)(3), Devleesschauwer B(1)(2)(9).

Author information:
(1)GBADs programme -, Liverpool, United Kingdom.
(2)Department of Epidemiology and Public Health, Sciensano, Brussels, Belgium.
(3)Department of Health Metrics Sciences, Institute for Health Metrics and 
Evaluation, University of Washington, Seattle, Washington, United States of 
America.
(4)Centre for Biosecurity and One Health, School of Veterinary Medicine, Harry 
Butler Institute, Murdoch University, Perth, Western Australia.
(5)Institute of Infection, Veterinary and Ecological Sciences, University of 
Liverpool, Liverpool, United Kingdom.
(6)Pengwern Animal Health Ltd, Wallasey Wirral, Merseyside, United Kingdom.
(7)Department of Population Medicine, Ontario Veterinary College, University of 
Guelph, Guelph, Ontario, Canada.
(8)Section of Epidemiology, Vetsuisse Faculty, University of Zurich, Zurich, 
